item.title: Hello
item.description: Hello, world! #include <stdio.h> int main(int argc, char *argv[]) { printf("Hello, world!"); } Another gravestone of the modern web. Are you still surprised to see some developer’s blogspam? Surprised that someone might think it’s worth the effort to manager their own personal website? Delusional enough to think they might drive traffic to their poorly maintained website, like it’s still the 90s? Well, here we are.
